-- Czech Stocks: New World Resources, Erste Bank Are Active
-- B y   D o u g l a s   L y t l e
-- 2012-02-08T16:08:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/czech-stocks-new-world-resources-erste-bank-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock  index 
rose to a five-month high, gaining 2.2 percent to 1,024.2 at the
close in  Prague .  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  New World Resources Plc  (NWR CP), the biggest Czech
supplier of coking coal, rose 3.8 percent to 161.85 in Prague
trading after Morgan Stanley reiterated its “overweight”
rating, saying the company is an “attractive buying
opportunity.”  Erste Group Bank AG  (RBAG CP) rose to the highest in four
months in Prague trading after Goldman Sachs Group Inc. raised
its target price for the lender’s Vienna-listed shares to 30
euros from 23 euros, according to a research report today, which
cited Erste as one of the “top picks” among euro-area lenders.
The stock advanced 4.7 percent to 487 koruna in Prague, the
highest level since Oct. 7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
